[[Probability Space]] is a [[Measure Space]] such that the [[Measure]] of the whole space is equal to one.

It is a [[Triple|Tuple]] $$(\Omega, \mathcal F, P)$$ consisting of:

* [[Sample Space]] $$\Omega$$
* A [[Ïƒ-algebra]] $$\mathcal F$$ on $$\Omega$$
* The [[Probability Measure]] $$P: \mathcal F \to [0, 1]$$